4">BBC Radio 4</a> in the United Kingdom, and in the Sea Area Forecast from=
 <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Met_%C3%89ireann" title=3D"Met =
=C3=89ireann">Met =C3=89ireann</a>, the Irish Meteorological Service. Met =
=C3=89ireann issues a "Small Craft Warning" if winds of Beaufort force 6 (m=
ean wind speed exceeding 22 knots) are expected up to 10 nautical miles off=
shore. Other warnings are issued by Met =C3=89ireann for Irish coastal wate=
rs, which are regarded as extending 30 miles out from the coastline, and th=
e Irish Sea or part thereof.=20
</p><p>"Gale Warnings" are issued if winds of Beaufort force 8 are expected=
. "Strong Gale Warnings" are issued if winds of Beaufort force 9 or frequen=
t gusts of at least 52 knots are expected. "Storm Force Warnings" are issue=
d if Beaufort force 10 or frequent gusts of at least 61 knots are expected.=
 "Violent Storm Force Warnings" are issued if Beaufort force 11 or frequent=
 gusts of at least 69 knots are expected. "Hurricane Force Warnings" are is=
sued if winds of greater than 64 knots are expected.<sup class=3D"noprint I=
nline-Template Template-Fact" style=3D"white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title=3D"Wikipedia=
:Citation needed"><span title=3D"This claim needs references to reliable so=
urces. (May 2023)">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup>
</p><p>This scale is widely used in the Netherlands, Germany,<sup id=3D"cit=
e_ref-18" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beau=
fort_scale#cite_note-18"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>18<span class=
=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> Greece, China, Taiwan, Hong Kong, Malt=
a, and Macau, although with some differences between them. Taiwan uses the =
Beaufort scale with the extension to 17 noted above. China also switched to=
 this extended version without prior notice on the morning of 15 May 2006,<=
sup id=3D"cite_ref-19" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.=
org/wiki/Beaufort_scale#cite_note-19"><span class=3D"cite-bracket">[</span>=
19<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup> and the extended scale wa=
s immediately put to use for <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Typho=
on_Chanchu" title=3D"Typhoon Chanchu">Typhoon Chanchu</a>. <a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hong_Kong" title=3D"Hong Kong">Hong Kong</a> and <=
a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Macau" title=3D"Macau">Macau</a> re=
tain force 12 as the maximum.<sup class=3D"noprint Inline-Template Template=
-Fact" style=3D"white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.or=
g/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title=3D"Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span=
 title=3D"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (May 2023)">cita=
tion needed</span></a></i>]</sup>
</p><p>In the United States of America, winds of force 6 or 7 result in the=
 issuance of a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Small_craft_advisor=
y" title=3D"Small craft advisory">small craft advisory</a>, with force 8 or=
 9 winds bringing about a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gale_war=
ning" title=3D"Gale warning">gale warning</a>, force 10 or 11 a <a href=3D"=
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Storm_warning" title=3D"Storm warning">storm =
warning</a> ("a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tropical_storm_war=
ning" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Tropical storm warning">tropical storm=
 warning</a>" being issued instead of the latter two if the winds relate to=
 a <a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tropical_cyclone" title=3D"Trop=
ical cyclone">tropical cyclone</a>), and force 12 a <a href=3D"https://en.w=
ikipedia.org/wiki/Hurricane_force_wind_warning" title=3D"Hurricane force wi=
nd warning">hurricane-force wind warning</a> (or <a href=3D"https://en.wiki=
pedia.org/wiki/Hurricane_Warning" class=3D"mw-redirect" title=3D"Hurricane =
Warning">hurricane warning</a> if related to a tropical cyclone). A set of =
red warning flags (daylight) and red warning lights (night time) is display=
ed at shore establishments which coincide with the various levels of warnin=
g.<sup class=3D"noprint Inline-Template Template-Fact" style=3D"white-space=
:nowrap;">[<i><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_n=
eeded" title=3D"Wikipedia:Citation needed"><span title=3D"This claim needs =
references to reliable sources. (December 2020)">citation needed</span></a>=
</i>]</sup>
</p><p>In Canada, maritime winds forecast to be in the range of 6 to 7 are =
designated as "strong"; 8 to 9 "gale force"; 10 to 11 "storm force"; 12 "hu=
rricane force". Appropriate wind warnings are issued by Environment Canada'=
s Meteorological Service of Canada: strong wind warning, gale (force wind) =
warning, storm (force wind) warning and hurricane-force wind warning. These=
 designations were standardised nationally in 2008, whereas "light wind" ca=
n refer to 0 to 12 or 0 to 15 knots and "moderate wind" 12 to 19 or 16 to 1=
9 knots, depending on regional custom, definition or practice. Prior to 200=
8, a "strong wind warning" would have been referred to as a "small craft wa=
rning" by Environment Canada, similar to US terminology. (Canada and the US=
A have the Great Lakes in common.)<sup class=3D"noprint Inline-Template Tem=
plate-Fact" style=3D"white-space:nowrap;">[<i><a href=3D"https://en.wikiped=
ia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:Citation_needed" title=3D"Wikipedia:Citation needed">=
<span title=3D"This claim needs references to reliable sources. (December 2=
020)">citation needed</span></a></i>]</sup>
</p>
<div class=3D"mw-heading mw-heading2"><h2 id=3D"Weather_scale">Weather scal=
e</h2><span class=3D"mw-editsection"><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket"=
>[</span><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=3DBeaufort_s=
cale&amp;action=3Dedit&amp;section=3D5" title=3D"Edit section: Weather scal=
e"><span>edit</span></a><span class=3D"mw-editsection-bracket">]</span></sp=
an></div>
<p>Beaufort's name was also attached to the Beaufort scale for weather repo=
rting:
</p>
<table class=3D"wikitable">

<tbody><tr>
<th>Symbol</th>
<th>Interpretation
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td>a</td>
<td>active
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>b</td>
<td>blue sky
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>c</td>
<td>detached clouds
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>d</td>
<td>drizzling rain
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>f</td>
<td>fog
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>g</td>
<td>dark, gloomy
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>h</td>
<td>hail
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>l</td>
<td>lightning
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>m</td>
<td>misty (hazy)
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>o</td>
<td>overcast
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>p</td>
<td>passing showers
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>q</td>
<td><a href=3D"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Squally" class=3D"mw-redirect"=
 title=3D"Squally">squally</a>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>r</td>
<td>rain
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>s</td>
<td>snow
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>t</td>
<td>thunder
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>u</td>
<td>ugly (threatening)
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>v</td>
<td>visibility (unusual transparency)
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td>w</td>
<td>wet, dew
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<p>In this scale the weather designations could be combined, and reported, =
for example, as "s.c." for snow and detached cloud or "g.r.q." for dark, ra=
in and squally.<sup id=3D"cite_ref-20" class=3D"reference"><a href=3D"https=
://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Beaufort_scale#cite_note-20"><span class=3D"cite-b=
racket">[</span>20<span class=3D"cite-bracket">]</span></a></sup>
</p>
